<br>
The key, like with most melees, is: MOVE! JBoots or SOW potions. Run him around in wide and narrow unpredictable windings, backwards preferrably. Gate! Levitate! Stay out of his reach.<br>
<br>
As someone above said: Think of it as a fight pet vs rogue. Let the pet wear him down bit by bit. I used a fire pet, he stayed out of the pets melee range but the pet nuked him ... not much (maybe 20HP per nuke) but constantly.<br>
<br>
If he tries to Instill Doubt, Poison or other time consuming things, nuke him. If he tries to kill the pet ... med and watch, then decide if you want to nuke him or summon another pet from a distance.<br>
<br>
After gating I even had time to bandage while he was looking for me. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
Edit: Duel him where you have enough space to move. I tried another rogue in the Freeport arena (given, he was 55) and I ran into the walls several times, which hindered my movements immensly.<br>
<br>
