much true for all fights.<br>
<br>
I'd suggest water or air pet if you don't have epic.  Water can backstab, air runs fast and will land more melee attacks.  Air + expedience is about 95% as fast as SOW, certainly enough to keep up with jboots.<br>
<br>
The big thing is just stay the hell away.  A good PvP rogue can basically backstab you from the front by timing their attack right as they run past you.  It's best to just stay out of range entirely.  Don't try to channel anything, don't even stop to cast until you see them stop.<br>
<br>
With enough running in frantic circles, they will almost certainly stop to fight your pet, that's when you turn and re-DS the pet if needed or just start nuking the rogue.  If the rogue turns to you, don't try to finish your nuke, just start running immediately.  The pet will get him eventually.<br>
