The 2/3 PVP nerf for spells was put in place because casters did SO much more damage than melees (this was back pre-kunark) so that they'd have a fighting chance against us...before the nerf (and recently after, even) a wizard could stand their ground against a warrior, get off a root, and burn him down where he stood without losing 30% life.  Now, some of the melees are doing a higher DPS than a full burning caster...maybe THEY should have a 2/3 nerf too! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ugrumples.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grumples</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 192<br> <font color=#333333>(2/11/02 3:28:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14.topic&index=11>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Mage vs Rogue</span><hr size=1> Yeah, they really need to readdress PvP balance in general.<br>
<br>
SK HT's are total BS, too.  An evencon SK will HT you for about 60-70% of your health.  He can nearly kill you in one HT if he uses the dicipline.  1 HT + 1 lifetap = dead caster.<br>
<br>
Also, with so much resist gear in the game, nobody really gets rooted these days, at least not without a tash+malo first and half the time you hit someone with char and they only lose a pixel of health.<br>
<br>
Any melee class can be an excellent PvP class.  Wizards and druids still top the SZ scoreboards, but they get kills mostly by surprising lower level casters.  When it comes to head to head combat, it's hard to beat a rogue, paladin, shadowknight or monk.  Unnerfed uberweapons that slash for a few hundred points of damage aren't much fun to fight.<br>
